  "texts": [
    "As a benchmark, we also include the correlations given by the (cross-validated) linear baseline model, and the random permutation baseline.",
    "Correlations over socio-demographic sub-populations are an interesting measure because they allow us to ignore the means.",
    "Even in the presence of a strong absolute bias, a LLM could be said to display some sociological capabilities if it were able to replicate the variations of answer probabilities observed in the survey data.",
    "For instance, on a given question a LLM could output more answers 'C' overall, but still have answer \"C\" predictions that vary in the same directions over subpopulations as in the survey data.",
    "Furthermore, these correlations are akin to regression models in the sense that they are measured on subpopulations defined by socio-demographic traits."
  ],
